<h1 style="font-size: 16px;">General Terms</h1>

<h2>1. Parties</h2>
<p><strong>Service Provider:</strong> Festilaw B.V., a company incorporated under Dutch law, acting as the "Responsible Person" within the meaning of EU product safety regulations.</p>
<p><strong>Client:</strong> hereinafter "Client" or the "Company".</p>
<p>Together referred to as "Parties".</p>

<h2>2. Appointment and Scope of Services</h2>
<p><strong>2.1</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Responsible Person Appointment: Client appoints Festilaw as its European Union Responsible Person for consumer products sold in the EU, as required by the EU General Product Safety Regulation (EU) 2023/988 (GPSR). Festilaw accepts this appointment. This Agreement serves as the written mandate for Festilaw to act as Client's authorized representative in the EU, in accordance with Article 4 of Regulation (EU) 2019/1020 (for harmonized products) and the GPSR for non-harmonized consumer products.</p>
<p><strong>2.2</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Scope of Services: Festilaw shall perform the following duties as a Responsible Person as mandated by EU law:</p>
<p><strong>2.2.1</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Product Compliance Assurance: Verifying that each or specific Client product intended for EU consumers meets applicable EU safety requirements under the GPSR. This entails a general oversight that products have undergone required risk assessments and comply with relevant safety standards. (Note: Festilaw will not independently test products or certify compliance but will rely on documentation and assurances provided by Client.)</p>
<p><strong>2.2.2</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;EU Contact Information: Providing a EU contact address (physical) and an electronic address (e.g. email) for consumer and authority inquiries, as required by EU law. Festilaw's name and EU address shall appear on Client's product labels, packaging, or accompanying documentation, and on Client's website as needed, to fulfill the legal requirement that an EU-based Responsible Person be identifiable to consumers and regulators. Festilaw will promptly notify client of any changes to this contact information.</p>
<p><strong>2.2.3</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Authority Liaison &amp; Market Surveillance: Acting as the point of contact for EU market surveillance authorities, including responding to inquiries from regulators and facilitating communication. Festilaw will cooperate with authorities during investigations or safety checks by providing required information and documentation. If an EU authority requests additional product information or takes issue with a product, Festilaw will inform Client and coordinate a timely response. Client must support Festilaw in these matters (see Section 4.2 on response timelines).</p>
<p><strong>2.2.4</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Incident and recall assistance: Assisting with product safety incidents, recalls, and notifications. If a Client product is found to pose risks or is deemed dangerous, Festilaw will advise on compliance steps and assist in notifying authorities via the EU Safety Gate system (Safety Business Gateway). Festilaw will notify authorities without undue delay of any serious risks, as required by law. In such cases, Festilaw will also help prepare any required public recall notices or corrective action plans in cooperation with client. Client remains responsible for executing recalls (e.g. withdrawing or repairing products) but must do so with Festilaw's guidance and in line with authority orders (see Section 4.3).</p>
<p><strong>2.2.5</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Label &amp; packaging review (Limited): Festilaw will verify that Client's product labels and packaging include the legally required information (e.g. Festilaw's contact details as Responsible Person, manufacturer name/address, product identifiers, any required warnings). Important: Festilaw's standard service does not include a full regulatory review of all label content or marketing claims. Ensuring that labels, user instructions, and packaging meet all applicable EU labeling regulations (beyond the presence of the Responsible Person's details) is the responsibility of Client, unless Client separately contracts Festilaw or another expert for such services. (This exclusion is further detailed in Section 5.4.)</p>
<p><strong>2.2.6</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual Access Check: Festilaw will conduct one annual meeting or review with the Client to assess to relevant product data. During this review, Festilaw and the Client shall examine EU sales and select one (1) to five (5) sample products to confirm that the required technical documentation is readily available and up to date. Where necessary to fulfil its obligations as EU Responsible Person and to demonstrate due diligence toward market surveillance authorities, Festilaw may retain a copy of the Client's technical documentation for up to ten (10) years following the termination or expiration of this Agreement, in accordance with applicable EU product safety regulations. Festilaw shall ensure appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the confidentiality, integrity, and security of the retained documentation.</p>
<p><strong>2.2.7</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Communication Verification: Festilaw will verify that Client's designated customer service email and contact mechanisms (especially the email printed on packaging or provided on Client's website for EU consumers) are working and monitored. This ensures that if EU authorities or consumers send safety-related inquiries or urgent communications (e.g. in case of a product recall), they will reach the appropriate contact. Festilaw will test these contact points once per year and confirm to Client that they function correctly for rapid communication.</p>
<p><strong>2.2.8</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Handling questions of regular consumers. Festilaw's EU contact details shall be displayed on packaging and online; any consumer inquiries received via these channels will be promptly logged and forwarded by Festilaw, and Client shall ensure accurate, timely responses in accordance with EU consumer law (Festilaw does not operate a consumer helpline beyond this forwarding function). Up to 2 hours annually of this support is free of charge.</p>

<h2>3. Fees, Payment, and Additional Services</h2>
<p><strong>3.1</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual fee: Client shall pay an annual fee for the Responsible Person services. This fee is due and payable within 30 days of invoice. The service year always runs from 1 January to 31 December. If Client starts the service during the calendar year rather than on 1 January, the first invoice will be pro-rata, covering only the remaining months of that calendar year until 31 December (for example, a Client starting in July will be invoiced for six (6) months). Festilaw shall then issue a new invoice for the full annual fee in January of each following year. The fee covers all the essentials of the Responsible Person role as described in this Agreement, including:</p>
<p>Provision of Festilaw's EU physical address and electronic address for product labeling and website listing (to meet the EU requirement of providing an EU contact): this includes permission for Client to print Festilaw's name and contact details on packaging, product inserts, and Client's EU-facing website.</p>
<p>The annual access meeting &amp; documentation check (Section 2.2) and a brief report of that check. The brief report is only provided to companies with a product catalogue exceeding 100 SKUs.</p>
<p>Inclusion of Festilaw's name and address on Client's website and materials, as needed for EU regulatory compliance (Festilaw will provide wording or files if required, e.g. a "EU Responsible Person" certificate or info for the site).</p>
<p>Verification of contact setup (Section 2.2, Communication Verification) to ensure recall communications would reach the right person.</p>
<p>Up to 2 hours of support/basic handling questions of regular consumers as described above [service 2.2.8].</p>
<p>Festilaw confirms it will not store or keep Client's confidential product data beyond what is necessary for the above services. Festilaw shall retain copies of all technical documentation and compliance records relating to Client's products for a period of ten (10) years following the termination or expiry of this Agreement, in accordance with applicable EU product safety regulations and its obligations as EU Responsible Person.</p>
<p><strong>3.2</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Hourly Rate Fees: Should Client require or request assistance beyond the scope of the annual service (for example, handling a complex product recall, extensive correspondence with authorities, or extra compliance consultations beyond the included 2 hours), such additional services will be billed at the following hourly rates:</p>
<p>Senior Support: EUR €145 per hour [table 3.1] (e.g. for Festilaw's senior compliance experts to interact with government officials, manage high-level communications with authorities, or lead a serious incident response).</p>
<p>Junior Support: EUR €100 per hour [table 3.1] (e.g. for more routine tasks such as drafting responses to consumer questions, doing basic research on regulations, or other junior-level support activities).</p>
<p>Festilaw will obtain confirmation from Client before performing any billable additional work. Client will be invoiced for additional support at the end of the month in which it was provided (or upon completion of a specific incident support task), with detailed time logs. Payment is due within 30 days of invoice.</p>
<p><strong>3.3</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Price Adjustments: The annual fee and hourly rates may be adjusted by Festilaw each year on the 1st of January. Client will receive written notice 30 days before any price change for a renewal term. If Client objects to the adjusted price, it may terminate the Agreement at the end of the then-current term by providing written notice (per Section 7.2), failing which the new prices will apply for the next renewal term.</p>
<p><strong>3.4</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Table of Service and Payment</p>
<p>Below is the specification of the Services. Festilaw assumes no responsibility for any activities not expressly included in, and paid for as part of, the Services purchased by Client. It is solely at Client's discretion which additional services it engages. Any non-compliance with EU law relating to Client's products or operations remains entirely at Client's risk and responsibility.</p>
